{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"deniable-pentagonal-yeti","description":"## Why\nThe cross-round convergence floors (plan-review rising floor + code-review region-gated floor) are being flipped to default-ON (ticket 70c8-423e-e4c1-4d86) by operator authorization. The flags (verify.remediation_mode, verify.novelty_drop_active) then exist only as a back-out. Once default-on has soaked in the field, the flags are dead configuration surface: remove them and make the floors always-on, per the operator directive.\n\n## What\n- Delete the `remediation_mode` and `novelty_drop_active` keys from src/rebar/_config_schema.py (fields + coercion entries) and remove every gate check that consults them (src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py, src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py, src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py) so the floor path is unconditional (per-review eligibility in plan_review/attest.py remains the only gate).\n- Remove/adjust the off-path tests (tests/unit/test_plan_review_rising_floor.py, test_plan_review_convergence.py, test_plan_review_remediation_gate.py, test_code_review_region_gate.py) that exercise flag-off behavior; keep eligibility-gate tests.\n- Update docs/config.md + docs/plan-review-gate.md (drop the keys from the tables; describe eligibility as the only gate). Note the unknown-key warning path will flag stale configs that still set them — acceptable per deprecation policy.\n- Precondition: a field soak of default-ON with no must-suppress regressions (e.g. one week of dogfood rounds, no gold-set suppression incidents).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The two config keys are removed from the schema and all consuming gate checks; the rising floor runs whenever per-review eligibility holds, with no config switch.\n- [ ] Off-path flag tests are removed/replaced; eligibility-path tests remain green; make lint && make typecheck && make test green.\n- [ ] docs/config.md and docs/plan-review-gate.md no longer document the keys and describe eligibility as the sole gate.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] a soak period with the floors default-ON has elapsed with no must-suppress (gold-set) regression reported; the attestation names the soak window and evidence.","id":"49ae-258b-4534-4d83","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Remove the convergence-floor flags: make remediation-mode rising floor always-on"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783830958830569001,"uuid":"a08b5fe7-7028-4172-b324-1890cb709606"}